President Joe Biden will attend the G7 Leaders' Summit in southern Germany on June 25. The summit will address various global issues, such as supporting Ukraine, economic and democratic resilience, climate change, infrastructure development, global health security, and the food and energy crisis caused by Russia's aggression. On June 28, President Biden will travel to Madrid, Spain for the 2022 NATO Summit. The summit will focus on endorsing a new Strategic Concept for NATO's transformation, including strengthening deterrence and defense, building resilience against transnational threats like cyber and climate change, and deepening partnerships with democratic allies in Europe and Asia to reinforce the rules-based international order.